#hackathon #physicalaibook #ragchatbot | Syeda Biya
Our hackathon project is based on Physical AI Humanoid Robotics integrated with a smart RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) Chatbot . This system is designed to make learning more interactive, intelligent, and reliable. The humanoid robot can understand human commands , respond naturally, and assist users in real time, while the RAG chatbot retrieves accurate information directly from the book instead of guessing answers . This ensures authentic, context-based, and trustworthy responses for students and researchers . By combining robotics, artificial intelligence, and knowledge retrieval, our project showcases the future of smart educational assistants and human-AI collaboration . Ameen Alam Ali Jawwad #Hackathon #PhysicalAIBook #RagChatbot

GIAIC Sunday Evening Students AI / Spec-Driven Online Hackathon 1 Submission Deadline: Sunday, Dec 7th @ 11:59 PM
Please note the Hackathon is starting right now, you should be ready with your Claude Code and Spec-Kit Plus setup and specs before the Hackathon day, however you will receive and update the title of the book to be generated on the evening of the hackathon i.e. Wednesday, Dec 3rd at 8 pm on the WhatsApp group mentioned below. Join WhatsApp Group Now all technical discussions, questions, etc. will be discussed here: https://chat.whatsapp.com/BHRGmTiu7a83hTgQoCwbWt (Only Sunday Evening Students) The title of the book for the project will be announced on this WhatsApp group at 8 pm on Wednesday, Dec 3rd This event requires you to complete a unified project using Claude Code (with any LLM model see reading material 1 so that you can use it for free) and Spec-Kit Plus. The core deliverables are: 1. AI/Spec-Driven Book Creation: Write a book using Docusaurus and deploy it to GitHub Pages. 2. Integrated RAG Chatbot Development: Build and embed a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) chatbot within the published book. This chatbot, utilizing the OpenAI Agents/ChatKit SDKs, FastAPI, and Qdrant Cloud Free Tier, must be able to answer user questions about the book's content, including answering questions based only on text selected by the user. Participants can earn bonus marks by creating reusable intelligence via Claude Code Subagents and Agent Skills (You can start working on it right now and use it on Sunday). We want to develop Matrix (Movie) like technology. See this where Trinity (Subagent) is learning/loading Helicopter Flying program (Skill, predefined reusable intelligence) in it's context, when required: https://youtu.be/SoAk7zBTrvo?si=uztOdaeIXDXtajLB The project will be evaluated out of 100 by one of the panel members including Asharib Ali, Naeem, Aneeq, Ameen, GIAIC Faculty, Class Coordinators, Zeeshan, Daniyal, Bashir, Imran, Zia, and others. On Sunday you will Submit your project here: https://forms.gle/3WcS1FHNUE8qFsUZ8 After submitting your project using this form, you will join the Zoom meeting.     • mene git in Install kia he fir bhi cmd me check karta hu to nahi ata he
  • Copy
  • Read Message
    • AITOPIA
    Agar aapne Git install kiya hai lekin command prompt (CMD) me "git" ko check karne par woh nahi aa raha, to yeh kuch possible solutions hain:
    1. PATH Variable Check Karein:
      • Aapko ensure karna hoga ke Git ki installation ka path aapke system ke PATH environment variable me included hai.
      • Isko check karne ke liye:
        • Windows Search me "Environment Variables" likhein.
        • "Edit the system environment variables" par click karein.
        • "Environment Variables" button par click karein.
        • "System variables" section me "Path" ko dhundhein aur edit karein.
        • Dekhein ke kya Git installation ka path (jaise C:\Program Files\Git\bin ya C:\Program Files\Git\cmd) wahan included hai. Agar nahi hai, to ise add karein.
    2. CMD Ko Restart Karein:
      • Kabhi-kabhi changes effect hone ke liye aapko command prompt ko restart karna padta hai. Command prompt ko band karein aur dobara kholen.
    3. Git Installation Verify Karein:
      • Aapko ensure karna hoga ke Git sahi se install hua hai. Aap "Programs and Features" me jaakar check karein ke Git listed hai ya nahi.
    4. Reinstallation:
      • Agar above steps se kaam nahi ban raha, to aap Git ko uninstall karke dobara install karne ki koshish karein.
    5. Version Check:
      • Install hone ke baad, aap command prompt me git --version command run karke verify kar sakte hain ke Git sahi se install hua hai ya nahi.
    Yadi in steps ke baad bhi aapko koi dikkat hoti hai, to aap yahan aur details share kar sakte hain.
